<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVE TRAIN - Installation - High-pressure Oil
        Rail System
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26504.4.12" graphiccount="7">
        <title>High-pressure Oil Rail System</title>
        <figure id="f26504103" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D08126.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Lubrication of top D-ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the D-ring in the top of the injector cavity with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f26504104" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D08127.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Alignment of oil rail assembly to oil inlets</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f26504106" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D08130.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil rail assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align oil rail assembly with oil inlets of each injector.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tilt oil rail assembly toward engine, align oil rail assembly with case-to-head tube
                assembly, and push down evenly until oil rail assembly is firmly seated.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Hand start M6 x 25 oil rail assembly bolts 1, 2, and 3 until finger tight.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f26504107" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D08131.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil rail assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f26504108" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D08132.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Torque sequence for oil rail bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Finish installing the remaining bolts finger tight. Torque bolts to the special torque
                following the sequence in .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="j2654109" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ31/J31334.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Crankcase-to-head tube assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase-to-head tube plug (long - with check valve)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase-to-head tube</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f2650417" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD31/D31509.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Crankcase-to-head tube plug (hex head)</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The square socket short crankcase-to-head tube plug and crankcase-to-head tube assembly is not
                    available for service.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, install new crankcase-to-head tube plug (long - with check valve) and
                    crankcase-to-head tube. D-rings are not replaceable.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, make sure the new crankcase-to-head tube bottoms out in the branch tube
                    assembly. This ensures that the oil rail, case-to-head tube assembly, and fuel injectors will
                    function correctly.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate D-rings on new crankcase-to-head tube assemblies with clean engine oil.</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Crankcase-to-head tube plug (long - with check valve)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Crankcase-to-head tube</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install new crankcase-to-head assemblies through high-pressure oil rail.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Torque crankcase-to-head assemblies to the special torque .</para>
        </step1>
